This is template edition of YARBS.
--archlinux--

-------
yurgs.csv - This file includes programs you want to have installed by the script.

TAGS and their meanings: 	empty - Will install program using `pacman`.
				G - Will clone repository, compile it using `make && sudo make install`. This requires git cloning URL.
				A - Will install program using `$aurhelper`.
				P - Will install program using `pip`.

FORMATTING:			tag,packagename/giturl,text
-------



-------
yarbs.sh - The main script.

Adding git repository URL:	You can add git cloning URL as a variable as shown in DEFAULTS category, or directly inside putgitrepo (line 21 and 247).
Changing welcoming and finalizing message: Change text inside quotes (line 36 and 192).
Execute custom function:	You can make your own function, which will be later executed by the script (line 179 and 265).
Enable custom services:		You can enable custom services using `systemd`. (line 272).
-------
